	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=2672&mid=10279536472089>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=2672&mid=10279536472089>I finally made the Trueshot</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=2672&mid=10279536472089#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jul 29th 10:53 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=165128><span id= >DinoDino</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Finally. I made the Trueshot Longbow this past weekend. And what a task it was to make. The amount of time and plat spent fletching almost makes the bow not worth-while. But making this bow is a 'rite of passage' for all rangers. I could have just bought this bow (it only sells for about 200 plat) but I wanted to make it (ok, I'm stubborn). I think every ranger should do this quest. It's what makes a ranger a ranger. But here's my advice before trying to make the Trueshot. Gather planty of materials. Try and get enough for at least 10 attempts. While gathering all of the components, be wary of the pirate on Erollisi Island and also be wary of the Minotaur Hero and the Kobold Missionary in Steamfont (all 3 killed me at one time or another). Always know where they are. If you like, you may make your first attempt at the Trueshot at fletching skill 100, but do not be disappointed when you end up with nothing. Remember, this is a tough quest and most people do not get the bow until much higher fletching skill. I would suggest waiting until your fletching skill is at least at 150 before making your first attempt. And then, depending on the amount of components that you have, you should try another attempt at every 10 skill levels after 150. I myself tried 1 attempt at 100, 1 attempt at 120, one attempt at 135, one attempt at 150 and failed every time (I made all of these attempst at these levels based on advice from web sites, guild members and other rangers buddies). I decided to go for 2 tries at skill level 165 and on my second try, I made it! I wasn't expecting to make the bow, so I think I may have been rather lucky. In fact, I've heard of some unfortunate rangers not being able to make the Trueshot until they hit level 200. Then again, I've also heard of (probably B.S.) lucky rangers making the Trueshot at level 70. Just be sure to gather planty of components and be very, very patient. </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
